<!-- §8 Why people are buying — problem this solves -->
<h2>Why Light Blocking and Pressure Actually Matter for Sleep</h2>
<p>Sleep quality depends on blocking light and calming your nervous system. Light suppresses melatonin production, keeping you awake; tension in your eyes and sinuses creates low-grade pain that disrupts REM sleep. A weighted eye mask tackles both at once, using blackout fabric to block light and gentle pressure to relax the muscles around your eyes and forehead. Add lavender aromatherapy and you've got a complete relaxation tool.</p>
