<!-- FAQ -->
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq supporting-questions">
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>How heavy is the weighted eye mask?</h3><p>It weighs approximately 200 grams (about 7 oz) — heavy enough to provide noticeable acupressure but light enough to be comfortable for all-night wear. Think of it as gentle pressure, not a heavy weight.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Does the lavender scent last?</h3><p>The lavender scent is strongest when new and gradually fades over several months. You can refresh it with a drop of lavender essential oil on the inner fabric. The mask is effective for sleep even without the scent.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Can I heat or cool this mask?</h3><p>The lavender fill makes it suitable for gentle warming (microwave 10-15 seconds) or cooling (refrigerator for 30 minutes). Do not freeze or overheat. Warm use is great for sinus relief; cool use helps with puffy eyes and migraines.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>How do I clean it?</h3><p>Spot clean only with a damp cloth. Do not machine wash or submerge, as this will damage the lavender fill and affect the weight distribution.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Will this work if I have a larger head or need a snug fit?</h3><p>The Heart Weighted Eye Mask has an adjustable strap, so it accommodates a range of head sizes. The mask fits securely without sliding during sleep. If you're concerned about fit, check the product dimensions and compare to similar sleep masks you may already own.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>How long will the weighted eye mask last before I need to replace it?</h3><p>With proper care (spot cleaning, no submersion), the mask should last 3-5 years. The lavender fill compacts over time, gradually reducing the weight by about 10-15% after 2-3 years. When the scent and pressure diminish significantly, replacement is appropriate.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Can I use this mask during naps or is it only for nighttime sleep?</h3><p>Absolutely for naps. The mask is versatile enough for 15-20 minute afternoon naps, meditation sessions, or migraine relief during the day. Many users keep it on their nightstand specifically for migraine flare-ups and quick rest periods.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Is the lavender scent overpowering or likely to bother me?</h3><p>The lavender scent is mild to moderate — present when you first put it on, but you'll adjust quickly. If you're sensitive to essential oils or prefer unscented products, the mask works just as effectively without the scent component once it fades after a few months.</p></div>
</div>

